pr_title: ci: added windows long tests
pr_body:
fixes #1745 
I ran the tests and looks like codecov does a perfect job merging the reports.
The coverage including both reports looks like this at the moment: https://codecov.io/gh/yashugarg/cve-bin-tool/tree/6ca8860bcdb74d300d64ed69a6930a7aa799a568

pr_title: feat: fuzzing json inputs for report merging
pr_body: I learned about importing `.proto` files and found exciting JSON functions so I tried them out in fuzzing MergeReports.

pr_title: feat: fixed MergeReports fuzzer.
pr_body:
@terriko, protobuf now uses default values for message fields, if not provided in the fuzzed data.
This should help make the MergeReport fuzzer run!

pr_title: refactor: restructure fuzzer
pr_body:
This PR revamps the current file structure of the `fuzz` module,
It also includes changes in generated protobuf files allowing all files to run similarly with:
`python -m fuzz.fuzz_foo`
